- Create streets table id, StreetName, StreetCode, WardCode, created_at, updated_at
- Remove column id from permission_role table
- Add three column zone_id, region_code and district_code to staffs table
- add default column to permissions with initial value 0 (false)

Run these statement direct to mysql (copy and paste);
------------ Start --------
ALTER TABLE MOE.applications CONVERT TO CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
CREATE INDEX region_uid_index ON MOE.regions (id,RegionCode);
CREATE INDEX district_uid_index ON MOE.districts (id,LgaCode);
CREATE INDEX ward_uid_index ON MOE.wards (id,WardCode);
CREATE INDEX street_uid_index ON MOE.streets (id,StreetCode);
CREATE INDEX school_establishment_indexes ON MOE.establishing_schools (id,school_category_id,tracking_number);
CREATE INDEX application_indexes ON MOE.applications (id,tracking_number);
CREATE INDEX maoni_indexes ON MOE.maoni (id,trackingNo,user_from, user_to);
--------------- End ------------
To Generate Roles and Permissions Run  http://ap_base_url/api/generate_roles_permissions  method: POST 
It will create two roles SuperAdmin and Admin with permissions list and permission_role
Update staff new_role that you want to login with SuperAdmin previllage give new_role=1